# REST API - Knowledge Transfer (KT)

**API Root URL:** `https://asfancynumber.com/fancy_number/api.php`

---

## 1. Overview
The API is designed as a dynamic CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) interface. You can interact with any of the 17 allowed tables by appending the table name to the root URL.

### Security
The API contains a **whitelist**. Only the following tables can be accessed:
`wp_users`, `wp_fn_dealers`, `wp_fn_number_types`, `wp_fn_number_categories`, `wp_fn_numbers`, `wp_fn_upload_batches`, `wp_fn_cart`, `wp_fn_orders`, `wp_fn_order_items`, `wp_fn_payments`, `wp_fn_sales_log`, `wp_fn_whatsapp_log`, `wp_fn_number_history`, `wp_fn_number_patterns`, `wp_fn_featured_numbers`, `wp_fn_dealer_sales`, `wp_fn_platform_commissions`.

---

## 2. API Endpoints & Usage

### A. List Records (GET)
Retrieve multiple records from a table.
- **URL:** `[ROOT]/[table_name]`
- **Example:** `https://asfancynumber.com/fancy_number/api.php/wp_fn_numbers`
- **Optional Params:** `?limit=50&offset=0`

### B. Get Single Record (GET)
Retrieve a specific record by its primary key ID.
- **URL:** `[ROOT]/[table_name]/[id]`
- **Example:** `https://asfancynumber.com/fancy_number/api.php/wp_fn_numbers/101`

### C. Create Record (POST)
Insert a new row into a table.
- **URL:** `[ROOT]/[table_name]`
- **Method:** `POST`
- **Body (JSON):**
  ```json
  {
      "mobile_number": "9988776655",
      "price": "5000.00",
      "dealer_id": 1
  }
  ```

### D. Update Record (PUT / PATCH)
Modify an existing record by ID.
- **URL:** `[ROOT]/[table_name]/[id]`
- **Method:** `PUT` or `PATCH`
- **Body (JSON):**
  ```json
  {
      "price": "4500.00",
      "status": "booked"
  }
  ```

### E. Delete Record (DELETE)
Permanently remove a record by ID.
- **URL:** `[ROOT]/[table_name]/[id]`
- **Method:** `DELETE`

---

