## 4. Push Data Examples (POST)

To "Push" data into any table, send a **POST** request to the table URL with a JSON body.

### 1. Users (`wp_users`)
```json
{
    "name": "Arun Kumar",
    "email": "arun@example.com",
    "phone": "9876543210",
    "password_hash": "hashed_pass_here",
    "role": "dealer"
}
```

### 2. Dealers (`wp_fn_dealers`)
```json
{
    "user_id": 5,
    "dealer_name": "Premium Numbers South",
    "phone": "9876543211",
    "whatsapp_number": "9876543211",
    "whatsapp_group": "South Fancy Group"
}
```

### 3. Number Types (`wp_fn_number_types`)
```json
{
    "type_name": "VVIP Gold",
    "description": "Exclusively for business high-fliers",
    "display_order": 1
}
```

### 4. Number Categories (`wp_fn_number_categories`)
```json
{
    "category_name": "Mirror Numbers",
    "description": "Numbers that read the same backwards"
}
```

### 5. Numbers Inventory (`wp_fn_numbers`)
```json
{
    "mobile_number": "9999911111",
    "type_id": 1,
    "category_id": 2,
    "dealer_id": 5,
    "price": "50000.00",
    "prefix": "99999",
    "pattern_type": "AAAAA",
    "digit_sum": 50,
    "repeat_count": 5
}
```

### 6. Upload Batches (`wp_fn_upload_batches`)
```json
{
    "file_name": "march_stock.csv",
    "uploaded_by": 1,
    "total_records": 5000
}
```

### 7. Cart (`wp_fn_cart`)
```json
{
    "user_id": 10,
    "number_id": 505,
    "expires_at": "2026-03-08 13:30:00"
}
```

### 8. Orders (`wp_fn_orders`)
```json
{
    "user_id": 10,
    "order_number": "ORD-2026-1001",
    "total_amount": "50000.00",
    "order_status": "pending",
    "payment_status": "unpaid"
}
```

### 9. Order Items (`wp_fn_order_items`)
```json
{
    "order_id": 1,
    "number_id": 505,
    "dealer_id": 5,
    "price": "50000.00"
}
```

### 10. Payments (`wp_fn_payments`)
```json
{
    "order_id": 1,
    "transaction_id": "TXN_998877",
    "payment_gateway": "RazorPay",
    "amount": "50000.00",
